{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 11:59:37.650091", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- Network health: Degraded. Only a single host pair can communicate; most intra-subnet reachability is broken.\\n- Control-plane: All OVS switches are connected to the controller. No physical link issues observed on data-plane ports.\\n- Data-plane: OpenFlow rules are misprogrammed (including self-loop outputs), causing widespread blackholing and ARP failures. Fail mode is secure, so there is no fallback forwarding.\\n\\nObserved reachability\\n- Successful:\\n  - host_1_2 (10.0.0.2) ↔ host_2_1 (10.0.0.3): ping succeeds with low RTT (~2–3 ms).\\n- Failing:\\n  - host_1_1 (10.0.0.1) to any (10.0.0.2/3/4): Destination Host Unreachable or no replies.\\n  - host_2_2 (10.0.0.4) to any: Destination Host Unreachable.\\n  - host_2_1 (10.0.0.3) to host_1_1 (10.0.0.1), host_2_2 (10.0.0.4): Destination Host Unreachable.\\n- ARP state corroborates partial connectivity:\\n  - Only 10.0.0.2 ↔ 10.0.0.3 show STALE neighbor entries; most others are FAILED.\\n\\nSwitch/controller status\\n- OVS bridges leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1:\\n  - Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" is_connected: true on all three.\\n  - fail_mode: secure on all three (unknown traffic is dropped if not explicitly allowed).\\n  - Data-plane ports eth0/eth1/eth2 report state LIVE; 10Gb full-duplex.\\n- OpenFlow rules (OF1.3) are anomalous:\\n  - leaf_1:\\n    - in_port=1 actions=output:1 (self-loop on eth0/port 1).\\n    - Pair-specific rules for dl_src=8a:5f:d7:67:7d:a2 (host_1_2) and dl_dst=de:38:de:7b:b3:70 (host_2_1), forwarding between ports 2 and 3.\\n  - leaf_2:\\n    - in_port=2 actions=output:2 (self-loop on eth1/port 2).\\n    - Pair-specific rules matching the same 8a:5f.. ↔ de:38:de.. MACs, forwarding between ports 1 and 3.\\n  - spine_1:\\n    - Only the two pair-specific rules for 8a:5f.. ↔ de:38:de.. between ports 1 and 2.\\n- No table-miss or general L2 bridging rules were observed; only narrowly scoped flows exist.\\n\\nTopology observations\\n- Described link (spine_1:eth2, leaf_1:eth3) is not present in port descriptors (spine_1 lists only eth0/eth1; leaf_1 lists eth0/eth1/eth2). This discrepancy likely reduces path redundancy but is not the primary cause of the observed failures, given one host pair works end-to-end through existing links.\\n\\nAnomalies identified\\n- Self-loop forwarding rules:\\n  - leaf_1: in_port=1 → output:1\\n  - leaf_2: in_port=2 → output:2\\n  These effectively reflect frames back to the ingress port, preventing proper broadcast/ARP propagation and isolating hosts on those ports (host_1_1 on leaf_1 eth0 and host_2_2 on leaf_2 eth1).\\n- Extremely narrow flow programming:\\n  - Flows exist only for one MAC pair (host_1_2 ↔ host_2_1). No rules for host_1_1 (b6:61:cf:c0:04:74) or host_2_2 (92:d2:21:73:24:ae), resulting in ARP failure and ping unreachability for these hosts.\\n- fail_mode secure with no table-miss to controller:\\n  - In secure mode, absent table-miss/default rules cause unknown traffic to be dropped rather than punted to the controller, further enforcing the blackhole for all unprogrammed flows.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Physical links and ports: Healthy (all relevant eth0/eth1/eth2 ports show LIVE).\\n- Data-plane behavior: Incorrect on leaf_1 and leaf_2 due to self-loop rules and missing forwarding entries.\\n- Control-plane: Controller connectivity is up, but the application logic is misprogramming flows (self-loops, incomplete host-pair coverage).\\n- Most probable faulty component: SDN controller policy/application at 20.0.0.100 (or its configuration), not the OVS switches themselves.\\n\\nLikely root cause\\n- Misprogrammed OpenFlow pipeline by the SDN controller:\\n  - Installation of self-loop rules on access ports (in_port X → output:X) causing ARP and unicast traffic to be reflected and dropped/ignored by hosts.\\n  - Absence of general L2 learning/bridging or table-miss entries; only a single MAC-pair path (host_1_2 ↔ host_2_1) is provisioned, leading to partial connectivity and neighbor resolution failures for all other hosts.\\n- Secondary note: The missing (spine_1:eth2 ↔ leaf_1:eth3) link deviates from the described topology but does not explain the selective connectivity; the core issue remains controller flow programming., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='81e12c7f-29a0-4a90-8078-b29a813dfa66'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
