{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 12:00:49.517474", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted solution:\n- Anomaly detected: true\n- Faulty devices: leaf_1, leaf_2\n- Root cause: flow_rule_loop\n\nRationale:\n- Self-loop OpenFlow entries (in_port -> output same port) on leaf_1 and leaf_2 cause ARP/broadcast reflection and isolation.\n- Extremely narrow, pair-specific rules leave most hosts without forwarding entries; with fail_mode=secure and no table-miss, traffic is dropped.\n- Controller is connected; issue is data-plane misprogramming on the leaves, consistent with a flow rule loop anomaly.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1949, "output_tokens": 121, "total_tokens": 2070, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
